CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 12, 1969, pg. 19, reads: "Keys' Dream 'Realized' - Brady Keys (L), former Steelers Pro Bowl selectee, and Buddy Young, celebrated Big Ten and NFL immortal, fix on a typical bootball.  The game has been most meaningful to both but Keys announced retirement at the Roosevelt Hotel on Monday, this week, to secure $250,000 Ford Foundation loan to his nation-wide All-Pro Chicken, Inc."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Steelers football player Brady Keys holding football and Buddy Young, standing behind table
